2-step process:

1) if not on NT, edit Makefile.ini, and remove all ^M chars from the
	ends of the lines: in vi, do as follows, where ^M means
	<control-v><control-m>:
		:%:s/^M//g
    ALTERNATIVELY:
	perl ../tools/ntclean.pl Makefile.ini


Do this: 
    chmod +x bootstrap.pl
    bootstrap.pl

or
    chmod +x bootstrap.pl
    perl bootstrap.pl


NB: Look for XXXX_XXXX in imakemdefs.h : there I just
overrode everything. You might have to fix this for other
architectures.

